13/05/2011
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Police announced on Thursday (May 12th) the arrest one of the closest associates of fugitive drug lord Darko Saric. Jovica Loncar was detained in Podgorica on suspicion of laundering Saric's money obtained from cocaine trafficking. Saric and his group already face charges in Serbia of smuggling 2.5 tonnes of cocaine from South America. In March, prosecutors filed fresh charges against them for money laundering and investing the drug money in Serbia's privatisation process. (Blic, Dan, Beta, RTCG - 12/05/11)
